<div><h3>GAME 225 - Mobile Game Production </h3>  <hr>This course explores the unique characteristics of developing and designing interactive media and games for mobile devices. Students will learn the various hardware and software appropriate for this platform as well as how to evaluate and address the challenges inherit in the technology. Lessons addressing the global audience as well as the rapidly expanding reach and influence of this dynamic distribution platform will be integral to the practical application of mobile development throughout the course.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Two semesters fo GAME 255<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Varies<br><br></div>		</td>
